{
  "bio": [
    "Ukrainian immigrant Michael Polsky founded Chicago-based Invenergy, one of the nation's biggest developers of renewable energy projects, 33 gigawatts so far.",
    "Invenergy is seeking to build the $11 billion, 800-mile transmission line across Kansas and Missouri called Grain Belt Expresss.",
    "Polsky made an early fortune selling natural gas generator SkyGen to Calpine for $450 million in 2001.",
    "Polsky has sold big multi-billion-dollar stakes in Invenergy to Blackstone and Canadian pension fund Caisse de Depot et Placement du Quebec.",
    "In 2006 an Illinois divorce court ordered him to pay wife Maya $180 million."
  ],
  "about": [
    "Polsky has given and pledged more than $150 million to the University of Chicago."
  ]
}